CBUILD RPM Source Tarball Lifecycle

  The CBUILD RPM source tarball lifecycle is a fascad on top of the standard
  autoconf lifecycle adding maven dependency management and project management.
  Patching is a big part of the lifecycle.  This project assumes you are not doing
  development, just packaging someone elses upstream work as a depedency. The table
  below shows the different phases of the RPM-STB Lifecycle and the goals
  (including standard maven goals) attached to them.

* Incomplete

  This is still being designed for the Beta release and will probably need to
  utilize remote-source-maven-plugin or project-sources-maven-plugin to get the
  source tarball of the upstream's project download site.  If
  project-sources-maven-plugin is used, remote-source-maven-plugin should be
  obsoleted.

